  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA135-kiḷavi">itu varaivu nīṭṭippa valarāmeṉak kavaṉṟa tōḻi ciṟaippuṟamākac colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante, who was anxious that there would be gossip if [HE] were to dealy marriage, said while [HE] was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA135">
<l>            tūṅka lōlai yōṅkumaṭaṟ peṇṇai</l>
<l>            māvarai putaitta maṇaṉmali muṉṟil</l>
<l>            varaiyāt tāram varuvirun tayarun</l>
<l>            taṇkuṭi vāḻna raṅkuṭic cīṟū</l>
<l>            riṉitumaṉ ṟamma tāṉē paṉipaṭu </l>
<l>            palcura muḻanta nalkūr pariya</l>
<l>            muḻaṅkutiraip putumaṇa laḻuntak koṭkum</l>
<l>            vāluḷaip polinta puravit</l>
<l>            tērōr nammoṭu nakāa vūṅkē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Pleasing indeed, alas, [was] it,</l>
<l>the little village with pretty homes for those who live in cool(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">taṇ kuṭi</term> does not really make sense here. The variant of ER, <term xml:lang="ta">taṉ</term>, is incongruent with <term xml:lang="ta">vāḻnar</term>, but I feel tempted to make an emendation to <term xml:lang="ta">taṅ kuṭi</term>: for those who live in their own homes.</note> homes,</l>
<l rend="indent">where they are engaged in [preparing] the coming feast with unlimited</l>
<l rend="indent4">rhythms,</l>
<l rend="indent2">in the front yard abounding in sand that has buried the big trunks</l>
<l rend="indent3">of the palmyra palms with high stems [and] hanging leaves</l>
<l>– before he had smiled with us, the one with the chariot,</l>
<l rend="indent3">with horses whose pure manes glittered,</l>
<l rend="indent">that revolved so that the new sand by the thundering waves</l>
<l rend="indent4">was impressed [by its wheels],</l>
<l rend="indent3">with poor motion, fatigued by many deserts, when the dew fell.<note place="foot">The construction of lines 6 and 7 is slightly asyndetic. We have to take <term xml:lang="ta">koṭkum</term> with the chariot (or rather with its - elliptical - wheels), but <term xml:lang="ta">pariya</term>, an adjective from <term xml:lang="ta">pari</term>, has to be connected with <term xml:lang="ta">puravi</term>.</note></l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="3b">
    <l>where the coming guests indulge themselves with unlimited food<note place="foot">Thus T.V.G.'s interpretation of the line.</note></l>
</lg>
        </lg>
         </div>
          </body>
        </text>
